1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:04,600
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:10,967
Never, ever use my child
to fix all of this.

3
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:13,033
You don't even care
that I could go to jail?

4
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:14,800
Face the consequences.

5
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:16,167
I'm going back to Iloilo.

6
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,200
I'm taking Ashley with me.

7
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:19,433
Signed.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,533
Does Edward know about this?

9
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:25,067
Do what you need to do.

10
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,033
My child will get better.

11
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:28,400
Ashley! Hey!

12
00:00:28,533 --> 00:00:29,633
Thea! Thea!

13
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:31,467
Ashley! Wait, wait!

14
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,233
Thea! Where are you taking
my child?

15
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,667
Why aren't they here yet?

16
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,933
Wasn't this scheduled earlier?

17
00:00:37,067 --> 00:00:38,633
They're not answering calls.

18
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:41,033
It's okay if it doesn't
push through.

19
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:44,400
I'm starting to accept
that this might really be it.

20
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,267
Maybe it's going to end soon.

21
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:50,600
[UNSETTLING]

22
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,300
Ashley.

23
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:39,500
Go to your room.

24
00:01:48,700 --> 00:01:50,800
One hundred fifty million pesos.

25
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:51,800
Just think about it!

26
00:01:51,933 --> 00:01:53,300
I've already decided.

27
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:55,100
Edward, this isn't just
about money.

28
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,333
Everything is about money
when you talk!

29
00:01:57,467 --> 00:02:00,600
But if we accept it,
I might not go to jail.

30
00:02:00,733 --> 00:02:02,533
Ashley could still be helped.

31
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:05,467
The chaos will be over
and our future will be secure.

32
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,500
- Your future.
- Ashley's future.

33
00:02:07,633 --> 00:02:09,033
Don't fool me!

34
00:02:09,167 --> 00:02:11,900
Don't pretend you're thinking
about Ashley's future.

35
00:02:12,033 --> 00:02:14,833
You're only thinking
about how to save yourself.

36
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:15,933
I'll be charged.

37
00:02:16,067 --> 00:02:17,300
I could go to jail.

38
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:18,467
Then if you did it,

39
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:21,033
face the consequences.

40
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:22,967
You don't even care
if I go to jail?

41
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:25,367
Because of what you did!

42
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:28,800
Never, ever use my child
to fix all of this.

43
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:32,433
- I'm not using Ashley.
- You use everything.

44
00:02:32,567 --> 00:02:33,700
And you?

45
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:35,600
What are you doing?

46
00:02:35,733 --> 00:02:38,133
You'll let Jasmine die
just to prove

47
00:02:38,267 --> 00:02:40,633
you're not controlled
by your father?

48
00:02:40,767 --> 00:02:44,433
Just to prove you won't give
Ashley up to her own father?

49
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:47,067
I can support Ashley on my own.

50
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,700
And I won't allow my child
to be sold

51
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:52,567
just to clear someone's
conscience!

52
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:55,633
By the end of the week,

53
00:02:55,767 --> 00:02:57,167
I'll go back to Iloilo

54
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,633
and take Ashley with me.

55
00:02:59,767 --> 00:03:01,767
- That's not allowed.
- I'm the legal father.

56
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:03,500
- I'm the mother!
- Who can be charged

57
00:03:03,633 --> 00:03:05,367
and imprisoned!

58
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:06,967
How will you take care
of my child?

59
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,800
There's nothing you can do
to stop me.

60
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:14,367
[INTENSE]

61
00:03:25,767 --> 00:03:28,267
Thank you, Mr. Torrecampo.

62
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,567
Thank you, Attorney.

63
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:32,933
[UNSETTLING]

64
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:37,500
Ah, Mrs. Torrecampo.

65
00:03:37,633 --> 00:03:38,900
[REGINA CHUCKLES]

66
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:46,533
What, what else did Attorney
Mamucod's associate do here

67
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:49,000
when there was
no legal settlement?

68
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,067
I fixed something.

69
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,133
I revised my will.

70
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,733
Huh?

71
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:58,633
What did you change?

72
00:03:58,767 --> 00:04:00,700
I should've done it earlier.

73
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,833
I removed Edward.

74
00:04:04,933 --> 00:04:06,233
What?

75
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:09,100
You removed your own son
from your will?

76
00:04:10,567 --> 00:04:12,833
I don't want anyone relying
on my name

77
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:15,533
while I'm being humiliated
in front of others.

78
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:19,667
He had the nerve to reject me.

79
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,133
After everything he's done?

80
00:04:22,267 --> 00:04:24,133
I offered him a family.

81
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:26,633
And then he just rejected me.

82
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:28,133
[SIGHS]

83
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:30,867
Edward refused to sell
his child.

84
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,533
That is not disrespect.

85
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:34,500
That is parenting.

86
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:37,700
That's not the point.

87
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:40,367
Then what's your
point, Greg?

88
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:44,100
I know you're worried
about Jasmine, so am I.

89
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:46,800
But try to understand Edward.

90
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,867
I've been understanding Edward
for a long time.

91
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,200
What you really mean is,

92
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,900
when you don't get your way,

93
00:04:54,033 --> 00:04:58,667
you make him feel he has no
right to be a father.

94
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,567
That's not parenting.

95
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,600
That's not being a parent.

96
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:04,233
That's settling a score.

97
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:07,200
He's a useless son,

98
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:09,600
so my being a father to him
is meaningless.

99
00:05:10,633 --> 00:05:11,933
If you think about it,

100
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:15,433
he never really had the right
to be in my will.

101
00:05:15,567 --> 00:05:16,867
What do you mean?

102
00:05:20,167 --> 00:05:20,967
Nothing.

103
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:23,400
I'm tired.

104
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:24,967
I need a drink.

105
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:30,533
[INTENSE]

106
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:44,700
[UNSETTLING]

107
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:00,367
Signed.

108
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:03,933
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

109
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,900
Does Edward know about this?

110
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:21,500
Edward and I have different
views on what's best for Ashley.

111
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:24,533
And as her mother,
I need to decide.

112
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:27,033
Thea,

113
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,833
are you sure about this?

114
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:32,200
Nothing is certain in our lives
right now.

115
00:06:33,333 --> 00:06:36,800
But I can stand by this more
than living with guilt.

116
00:06:36,933 --> 00:06:40,067
Because a child would be left
to die otherwise.

117
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:44,067
[INTENSE]

118
00:06:45,633 --> 00:06:46,833
Thank you.

119
00:06:52,433 --> 00:06:54,933
Please do what needs to be done.

120
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:57,367
Just let me know
Ashley's schedule.

121
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:02,733
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

122
00:07:15,967 --> 00:07:18,133
My child's condition will
improve.

123
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:24,500
She'll get better.

124
00:07:28,933 --> 00:07:32,367
The procedure will take three
to four hours, then observation.

125
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,033
I'll be there with you.

126
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:37,033
Mom, thank you.

127
00:07:38,533 --> 00:07:39,467
For what?

128
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,933
For choosing the right thing.

129
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:48,200
I know it wasn't easy for you.

130
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:50,100
After what I did.

131
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:53,533
What I said to Aunt Marj.

132
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:56,367
[DRAMATIC]

133
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:03,133
You don't have to apologize
for telling the truth.

134
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:07,367
I was hurt, yes.

135
00:08:08,867 --> 00:08:11,833
But I was more hurt when I
taught you to fear consequences

136
00:08:11,967 --> 00:08:13,400
instead of doing what's right.

137
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,700
But Mom, what about Dad?

138
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:24,333
I don't know how to face
your father.

139
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:28,600
But my child,
Jasmine needs you now.

140
00:08:32,567 --> 00:08:33,500
Let's go.

141
00:08:33,633 --> 00:08:34,867
I don't want you to be late.

142
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,500
You need to rest.

143
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:40,933
Ashley?

144
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,800
Ashley!

145
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:44,200
Hey! Thea!

146
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:45,333
Thea!

147
00:08:45,467 --> 00:08:47,200
Ashley! Wait, wait!

148
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:48,367
Thea, hey!

149
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,033
Where are you taking my child?

150
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:51,000
Ashley!

151
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:53,967
Open the window! Please, please!

152
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,967
Listen to Dad, please.

153
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:57,433
Please, Ash!

154
00:08:57,567 --> 00:08:58,833
Ashley!

155
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:00,933
Come on! Ashley! Ashley!

156
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:02,933
[GRUMBLES]

157
00:09:03,067 --> 00:09:07,600
[INTENSE]

158
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,767
- Paolo, are they coming?
- [LINE RINGING]

159
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:16,933
[LINE RINGING]

160
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:18,633
They're still not answering
the call.

161
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:21,100
<i>We're sorry, the number
you have reached...</i>

162
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:22,767
Call again.

163
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,967
[LINE RINGING]

164
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:29,033
Shouldn't they be here by now?

165
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:32,133
Ma'am, the prep team is ready.

166
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:33,233
[STAMMERS]

167
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:34,333
They'll arrive soon.

168
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:36,367
Okay, yes.

169
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:41,200
- [LINE RINGING]
- [INTENSE]

170
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:45,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:50,400
[INTENSE]

172
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,667
Your dad didn't follow us,
did he?

173
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,833
We got here first?

174
00:09:57,967 --> 00:10:00,600
Not really, He couldn't
follow anymore.

175
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:02,433
He can't stop us anymore.

176
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,533
We need the money, my child.

177
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:05,600
What?

178
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,067
Once this is settled,

179
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,933
we'll be out of this mess.

180
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:12,200
Our life will be better even
if it's just the two of us.

181
00:10:13,233 --> 00:10:15,733
And he won't be able
to interfere anymore.

182
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:17,867
He won't be able to take you
away from me.

183
00:10:19,367 --> 00:10:21,367
Mom, I'm scared.

184
00:10:24,067 --> 00:10:25,367
- Ashley!
- [SQUEALS]

185
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,433
- [LOUD CRASH]
- [HORN HONKING]

186
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:28,533
[INTENSE]

187
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,533
Nurse, excuse me.

188
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:33,700
Thea, Ashley Torrecampo.

189
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,033
- Car accident.
- [STAMMERS]

190
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,867
- Where are they?
- Sir Edward Torrecampo?

191
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,667
I was the one who called you,
Sir.

192
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,100
Yes, yes, that's me.

193
00:10:40,233 --> 00:10:42,733
Sir, your wife is stable now.

194
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:45,133
We're just monitoring her.

195
00:10:45,267 --> 00:10:46,333
My child, Ashley.

196
00:10:46,467 --> 00:10:47,333
Where is she? How is she?

197
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:48,500
Take me to her.

198
00:10:48,633 --> 00:10:49,967
She's being assisted right now.

199
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,900
It's best if the doctor
explains everything.

200
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,600
Why is this happening?

201
00:10:56,733 --> 00:11:00,000
[INTENSE]

202
00:11:04,733 --> 00:11:06,033
Why aren't they here yet?

203
00:11:06,167 --> 00:11:08,667
Wasn't this scheduled earlier?

204
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,767
- [NOTIFICATION CHIMES]
- They're not answering calls.

205
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:12,333
Wait, here.

206
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:13,367
They texted.

207
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,967
What did it say?

208
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:19,567
There was a minor car accident.

209
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,400
They said they're okay.

210
00:11:24,733 --> 00:11:27,467
We need to know the full details
if Ashley is really okay,

211
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:30,333
and why they aren't answering
our calls.

212
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:31,600
So what does this mean?

213
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,400
It won't push through again?

214
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:39,167
Paolo, why is it like this?

215
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:40,433
[SOBBING]

216
00:11:40,567 --> 00:11:43,533
Every time Jasmine has hope,

217
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:46,600
something always happens.

218
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:48,033
First, a delay.

219
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:50,500
Then, a compatibility scare.

220
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:52,767
And now, an accident?

221
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:54,200
Why does it feel like
something's stopping this?

222
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:57,267
Why does it feel like they don't
want my child to get better?

223
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:01,767
Why won't they let Jasmine heal?

224
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,200
[INTENSE]

225
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:07,667
[SOBBING]

226
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:15,867
Thea!

227
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:17,900
Hey, Thea!

228
00:12:18,033 --> 00:12:19,567
What do you think you're doing?

229
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:20,700
[HUFFS]

230
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,800
Really, Edward?

231
00:12:22,933 --> 00:12:24,067
Really?

232
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,400
I got into an accident too!

233
00:12:26,533 --> 00:12:27,867
Whose fault was it?

234
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,500
You were driving, right?

235
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,800
You were rushing to get away
from me.

236
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:34,400
You told me you
were taking Ashley.

237
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:35,567
What, you were running
to the hospital

238
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:38,733
because you want Ashley
to donate bone marrow?

239
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,000
Look at this.

240
00:12:40,133 --> 00:12:43,133
In the end, you're in the
hospital because of your greed.

241
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:44,767
You want to take her from me

242
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,467
because of money!

243
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,267
I didn't mean to.

244
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,833
But, hey, Thea, what do you mean
you didn't mean to?

245
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:54,467
You never mean any of it!

246
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,733
You didn't mean to deceive me,

247
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:58,767
you didn't mean to use Paolo.

248
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:01,467
You didn't mean to use
our child.

249
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:05,367
I don't want to lose her,
so I'll do everything

250
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,833
so we can live together
and properly!

251
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:10,333
- [THUMPS]
- Do you hear yourself?

252
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,200
You say you don't want
to lose her,

253
00:13:13,333 --> 00:13:17,133
but you're the reason
she almost died!

254
00:13:18,633 --> 00:13:19,700
Thea!

255
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,500
She's our child!

256
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:25,100
Our child!

257
00:13:26,367 --> 00:13:28,633
She's not an investment.

258
00:13:28,767 --> 00:13:30,567
She's not a bargaining chip.

259
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:33,167
She's not an insurance policy.

260
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,467
She's our child!

261
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:37,000
Our child!

262
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:38,900
What?

263
00:13:39,033 --> 00:13:40,333
You have nothing to say?
What, Thea?

264
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:41,367
Answer me!

265
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,000
What do you want to say?

266
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,733
I love Ashley!

267
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:53,567
If you love her,

268
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,300
start thinking about what's best
for her.

269
00:13:57,567 --> 00:14:00,300
Not just what you think
is good for you.

270
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,800
Because if something bad happens
to Ashley

271
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:10,700
because of your decisions,

272
00:14:12,667 --> 00:14:15,167
I won't be the only one who
won't forgive you.

273
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,533
You won't forgive
yourself either.

274
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:20,000
If you have a conscience.

275
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:26,067
[INTENSE]

276
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:30,133
My child, I'm sorry.

277
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:32,033
[SOBBING]

278
00:14:32,167 --> 00:14:34,300
This is my fault.

279
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:38,800
I pushed you to donate

280
00:14:38,933 --> 00:14:41,733
even though I knew your dad
was against it.

281
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:49,900
If it weren't for me,

282
00:14:50,033 --> 00:14:52,933
you wouldn't have been put
in danger like this.

283
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:57,767
I'm sorry.

284
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,133
Mom, I wanted this too.

285
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:05,233
You didn't force me.

286
00:15:05,367 --> 00:15:06,400
No.

287
00:15:09,133 --> 00:15:10,733
I'm your mother.

288
00:15:12,667 --> 00:15:15,067
I'm the one who
should protect you.

289
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:18,233
I shouldn't allow

290
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:21,133
your life to be risked even if
it's for Jasmine.

291
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:22,967
- But, Mom...
- That's enough, Ash.

292
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:26,533
We won't talk about
this anymore.

293
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,867
- But Jasmine is my sibling...
- And me?

294
00:15:30,167 --> 00:15:32,033
I'm not your real father.

295
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:34,467
So my opinion
doesn't matter anymore?

296
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,767
So it doesn't matter
what's good for you?

297
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:41,700
It's not like that, Dad.

298
00:15:41,833 --> 00:15:44,000
I just don't want her to die.

299
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:45,800
I love Jasmine.

300
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:47,733
So if there's something
I can do,

301
00:15:47,867 --> 00:15:50,700
even if it hurts,
even if it's scary,

302
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:52,700
why wouldn't I do it?

303
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,433
Child, just listen.

304
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:59,400
[DRAMATIC]

305
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:03,433
Wait...

306
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:04,833
It hurts, Mom!

307
00:16:04,967 --> 00:16:06,933
- Huh?
- What happened?

308
00:16:07,067 --> 00:16:10,333
- My foot hurts!
- Where?

309
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:12,400
Don't move it.

310
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:13,867
[GRUNTING]

311
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,867
- Edward!
- My foot hurts!

312
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:19,067
- Wait, wait.
- My foot hurts.

313
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,467
Doctor!

314
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,767
- [GRUNTS]
- Mom, my foot hurts so much!

315
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:24,667
It looks like her right foot
is sprained, Doctor.

316
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,433
It hurts!

317
00:16:26,567 --> 00:16:27,600
Where exactly does it hurt?

318
00:16:27,733 --> 00:16:29,167
- Where?
- Here.

319
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,633
- It hurts so much, Dad.
- [SOBBING]

320
00:16:31,767 --> 00:16:34,033
Can you lift her leg?

321
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:35,500
I can't.

322
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:38,500
Okay, on a scale of one to
ten, how painful is it?

323
00:16:38,633 --> 00:16:39,600
Ten being the highest.

324
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:40,800
Ten!

325
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:43,933
Does it hurt here?

326
00:16:44,067 --> 00:16:44,933
No.

327
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,500
- How about here?
- No.

328
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:48,233
- How about here?
- No.

329
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:50,500
- How about here?
- That hurts!

330
00:16:50,633 --> 00:16:52,333
I don't want this anymore!

331
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:54,067
Okay, let's not move her
for now.

332
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,567
Let's keep her immobilized.

333
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,967
We'll run a series of tests
and X-rays

334
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,200
and refer you to an orthopedic
specialist.

335
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:02,733
We'll be right back.

336
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:06,233
- It hurts so much.
- [SOBBING]

337
00:17:06,367 --> 00:17:11,400
[INTENSE]

338
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,300
How is Ashley?

339
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,967
Are you checking if she's okay?

340
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:26,633
Or are you checking if
the donation can still proceed?

341
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:30,300
[STAMMERS]

342
00:17:30,433 --> 00:17:33,233
Edward, don't say things
like that.

343
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,167
Of course we're worried.

344
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:36,733
I'm sorry, Marj.

345
00:17:36,867 --> 00:17:39,033
But the donation won't proceed.

346
00:17:39,167 --> 00:17:40,433
Forget the agreement.

347
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:42,300
Huh?

348
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:44,933
Wait, didn't you commit?

349
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:47,133
Why are you backing out now?

350
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:49,500
Thea, our agreement was clear.

351
00:17:49,667 --> 00:17:53,867
This isn't a dinner reservation
you can just cancel.

352
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,433
Wait.

353
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:57,233
My child got injured.

354
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:59,467
You still want her operated on
even though we don't know

355
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,867
the effects of the accident
on her?

356
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,633
You cannot back out now.

357
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:05,333
It's already scheduled.

358
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:06,400
We're out of time.

359
00:18:06,533 --> 00:18:07,800
Everything's arranged.

360
00:18:07,933 --> 00:18:10,800
We might lose our child
if you back out.

361
00:18:10,933 --> 00:18:13,633
My child was in an accident!

362
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:15,833
She's still a child!

363
00:18:15,967 --> 00:18:18,000
And because of what happened,

364
00:18:18,133 --> 00:18:20,467
I won't allow her life to be
risked again

365
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,200
no matter who it's for.

366
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:25,200
It's easy for you
to say that

367
00:18:25,333 --> 00:18:27,467
because you're not the one
watching your child

368
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:31,167
slowly weaken day by day.

369
00:18:31,300 --> 00:18:32,767
Why?

370
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:36,733
Do you think it's easy for me
that my child almost got hurt?

371
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:37,833
Enough.

372
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:41,100
Leave!

373
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:43,000
Leave my child alone!

374
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:44,433
- [STAMMERING]
- Marj, let's go.

375
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:45,667
No! Wait, just a moment!

376
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,100
This can't happen!

377
00:18:47,233 --> 00:18:48,200
- Stop it!
- Ashley.

378
00:18:49,433 --> 00:18:50,300
- Ashley.
- Leave my child alone!

379
00:18:50,433 --> 00:18:51,800
- Ashley, listen to me.
- Marj, just stop.

380
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:55,000
You're our only hope
to save Jasmine, please.

381
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:56,333
You saw her again, didn't you?

382
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:58,333
You saw how much
she's suffering.

383
00:18:58,467 --> 00:18:59,700
Ashley, listen to me.

384
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:01,100
Don't let her die.

385
00:19:01,233 --> 00:19:02,533
- Please have mercy.
- Enough.

386
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:03,967
- Nurse.
- Get out of here!

387
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:05,300
This is for my child.

388
00:19:05,433 --> 00:19:07,400
- I don't care about your child!
- Ashley, please.

389
00:19:07,533 --> 00:19:08,433
Sweetheart, don't listen
to Marj.

390
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:10,433
Ashley, please, listen to me.

391
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:13,667
If you truly love your sibling,
please help her.

392
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:14,800
- Let's go.
- I'm so sorry.

393
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:17,367
We won't allow this,
Don't agree to this!

394
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,733
- Ashley.
- Get out!

395
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:21,500
- [CLAMORING]
- Yes, I'll handle it.

396
00:19:21,633 --> 00:19:23,867
Ashley, please help Jasmine.

397
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,800
- Marj, please, lets go.
- Ashley.

398
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:30,033
[DRAMATIC]

399
00:19:39,467 --> 00:19:41,167
Is Ashley okay?

400
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,233
Thank God.

401
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:51,033
After my meeting with the
charity event organizer,

402
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:53,233
I'll go there immediately

403
00:19:53,367 --> 00:19:57,500
to check on Ashley and Jasmine
as well.

404
00:19:57,633 --> 00:20:00,333
[DRAMATIC]

405
00:20:08,167 --> 00:20:09,700
[CLEARS THROAT]

406
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:12,467
Is everything all right,
Mrs. Torrecampo?

407
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:17,500
[SIGHS]

408
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:20,600
My two grandchildren
are in the hospital,

409
00:20:20,733 --> 00:20:22,767
and my two sons who are...

410
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:25,767
Anyway,

411
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:28,600
what are you doing here?

412
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:31,233
Do you have a client meeting?

413
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:37,333
Well, it just ended, actually.

414
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:40,333
It seems the client isn't
interested in the property.

415
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:42,700
Seemingly, the exterior
looks good,

416
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:45,000
but when it comes
to the foundation,

417
00:20:45,133 --> 00:20:48,900
it seems there were issues
during construction.

418
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:52,433
Torrecampo Realty's properties
are usually solid.

419
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:55,767
Are you sure it's the foundation
that's the problem?

420
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:00,033
Well, when it comes to family,
Mrs. Torrecampo,

421
00:21:00,167 --> 00:21:03,567
no matter how good
the exterior looks,

422
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,767
if the foundation has issues,

423
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:08,167
the parents won't last.

424
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,867
Everything collapses,

425
00:21:10,033 --> 00:21:11,800
and the children suffer.

426
00:21:14,033 --> 00:21:17,700
Wait, I'm not sure anymore
whether

427
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:23,367
you're judging the property
or my foundation...

428
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,400
Not the family.

429
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:26,900
Forgive me, Mrs. Torrecampo.

430
00:21:27,033 --> 00:21:28,467
I wasn't referring to you.

431
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:30,200
I was speaking in general.

432
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:32,500
I know I talk a lot.

433
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:36,733
I'm sorry, many say I take after
my father.

434
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:38,300
Relax, Aldrin.

435
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:41,167
I know you didn't mean
to offend.

436
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:44,200
I'm actually lucky to
have gained a new friend.

437
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:45,867
[CHUCKLES]

438
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:49,167
Thank you for never getting
tired of listening to me.

439
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,267
[CHUCKLES]

440
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:54,500
Your father raised you
really well.

441
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:56,433
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

442
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:57,733
Excuse me.

443
00:21:57,867 --> 00:22:01,267
[INTENSE]

444
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:14,567
[COUGHING]

445
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:18,433
Here this, this.

446
00:22:19,533 --> 00:22:21,433
[MUMBLES]

447
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,233
[SIGHS]

448
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:39,867
[JASMINE SIGHS]

449
00:22:41,433 --> 00:22:43,167
- Mom?
- Yeah?

450
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:47,267
I thought I was getting
the transplant today?

451
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:51,767
[DRAMATIC]

452
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:56,800
What happened?

453
00:22:56,933 --> 00:22:58,033
There's just a slight delay.

454
00:22:58,167 --> 00:22:59,900
The doctor is fixing something.

455
00:23:01,633 --> 00:23:03,667
Because of Ashley?

456
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,767
Did she back out?

457
00:23:05,900 --> 00:23:09,700
[INTENSE]

458
00:23:13,533 --> 00:23:14,200
It's okay, Mom.

459
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,300
I'm starting to accept that

460
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:19,167
this might really be how it is.

461
00:23:20,967 --> 00:23:22,833
Maybe it's going to end soon.

462
00:23:24,033 --> 00:23:25,900
It's okay if it doesn't
push through.

463
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:27,200
No.

464
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:30,267
Jasmine, don't say that.

465
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,433
I've already accepted it, Mom.

466
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,833
This feels better so

467
00:23:34,967 --> 00:23:36,833
I won't be scared anymore.

468
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:41,100
No, my child,
we'll keep fighting.

469
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:44,567
These past few days,

470
00:23:45,733 --> 00:23:47,700
I got to be with you
and Dad again.

471
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:52,300
No one was fighting.

472
00:23:52,433 --> 00:23:54,233
We were bonding.

473
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:57,600
We even did DIY stargazing.

474
00:23:57,733 --> 00:24:00,800
[DRAMATIC]

475
00:24:00,933 --> 00:24:03,800
I finally felt like we were
a happy family again.

476
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:06,700
After so long.

477
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:11,933
I really appreciate it.

478
00:24:12,067 --> 00:24:13,667
Thank you for trying.

479
00:24:14,967 --> 00:24:16,467
My child,

480
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:19,500
this isn't where
your fight ends.

481
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:21,600
We still have so many plans.

482
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:23,900
I'm tired of hoping too, Dad.

483
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:26,833
I just want to rest.

484
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:30,700
With you and Mom beside me.

485
00:24:31,767 --> 00:24:35,700
[DRAMATIC]

486
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:38,567
[SOBBING]

487
00:24:41,433 --> 00:24:43,567
[SOBBING]

488
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:48,733
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

489
00:24:54,167 --> 00:24:55,433
We've run out of groceries.

490
00:24:55,567 --> 00:24:57,033
I'll just stop
by the supermarket.

491
00:24:57,167 --> 00:24:59,833
Is there anything you want me
to get?

492
00:24:59,967 --> 00:25:02,233
Nothing, Mom, I'm fine.

493
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:07,000
Maybe I should wait for your dad
before I go,

494
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:09,967
so you won't be alone?

495
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,600
Dad just left.

496
00:25:11,733 --> 00:25:15,033
He might take a while
to get here.

497
00:25:15,167 --> 00:25:18,033
And you might hit traffic, Mom,

498
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:19,900
if you leave later.

499
00:25:20,033 --> 00:25:24,133
[DRAMATIC]

500
00:25:24,267 --> 00:25:26,533
Don't worry about me, Mom.

501
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:29,500
It's also hard for me
to move with this foot.

502
00:25:31,133 --> 00:25:32,667
I'll just take a nap.

503
00:25:34,467 --> 00:25:35,367
[SIGHS]

504
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:36,967
All right.

505
00:25:37,100 --> 00:25:39,100
Just wait for your dad here.

506
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:42,933
Take care.

507
00:25:49,433 --> 00:25:54,933
[INTENSE]

508
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:08,433
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

509
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:22,800
Thea!

510
00:26:22,933 --> 00:26:23,800
Where's Ashley?

511
00:26:23,933 --> 00:26:25,000
She's in her room.

512
00:26:25,133 --> 00:26:27,233
I just checked she's not there.

513
00:26:27,367 --> 00:26:30,000
Was Ashley just pretending
that her foot still hurt?

514
00:26:30,133 --> 00:26:31,533
But where would she go?

515
00:26:31,667 --> 00:26:33,467
I only know one place
she'd go to.

516
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:36,633
Please don't, Uncle,
Dad doesn't know that I'm here.

517
00:26:36,767 --> 00:26:38,600
I just lied to you.

518
00:26:38,733 --> 00:26:39,967
What?

519
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,300
You just ran away?

520
00:26:41,433 --> 00:26:43,000
You have no shame!

521
00:26:43,167 --> 00:26:47,300
If anything happens to my child,
I'll make you pay!

522
00:26:47,433 --> 00:26:50,067
Paolo, you and Ashley should not
have lied!

523
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,600
Would you stop her if you knew

524
00:26:51,733 --> 00:26:54,100
Thea never really agreed
to the transplant?

525
00:26:54,233 --> 00:26:55,600
Marj, I'm not saying

526
00:26:55,733 --> 00:26:58,200
what we did was entirely right.

527
00:26:58,333 --> 00:27:00,000
But what choice do we have?

528
00:27:00,133 --> 00:27:02,033
Our child's life is at stake.

529
00:27:02,167 --> 00:27:06,533
We have no right to override
Ashley's parents.

530
00:27:06,667 --> 00:27:08,267
I have rights over her.

531
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,567
You don't get it, Paolo.

532
00:27:09,700 --> 00:27:10,867
This is karma catching up
to you.

533
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,967
Your karma is your child dying

534
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:16,367
because you're greedy,
deceitful, and arrogant!

535
00:27:16,533 --> 00:27:19,333
[INTENSE]
